The African National Congress (ANC) leadership says its election manifesto will respond to the challenges of crime and unemployment in the country. The party’s leadership was briefing the media in Durban ahead of the launch of the ANC’s election manifesto at the Moses Mabhida stadium in the city on Saturday. The ANC leadership says it is ready for its election manifesto launch, with all safety measures in place. Thousands of ANC supporters are expected to attend the event. ANC Secretary General Ace Magahsule says those attending the event will be expected to adhere to all rules of safety and order. “All control measures have been put in place to ensure that people are safe and tomorrow we’ll also prohibit items such as fire arms, dangerous weapons, no alcohol, as well as any t-shirt or placard that are insulting.” Click video below: 